gurmukhi: ਅਾਦਿ ਕੈ ਅਨਾਦਿ ਅਰ ਅੰਤਿ ਕੈ ਅਨੰਤ ਅਤਿ ਪਾਰ ਕੈ ਅਪਾਰ ਨ ਅਥਾਹ ਥਾਹ ਪਾੲੀ ਹੈ
transliteration: Aadi Kai Anaadi Ar Anti Kai Anant Ati , Paar Kai Apaar N Adaah Daah Paaee Hai ?
translation: As the imperishable God is beyond beginning though He is the beginning of all; as He is beyond end since He is the end of all; as He is beyond the farthest conceivable extent as He is unfathomable, so is the praise of the True Guru just like that of Lord.

gurmukhi: ਮਿਤਿ ਕੈ ਅਮਿਤਿ ਅਰ ਸੰਖ ਕੈ ਅਸੰਖ ਪੁਨਿ ਲੇਖ ਕੈ ਅਲੇਖ ਨਹੀ ਤੌਲ ਕੈ ਤੌਲਾੲੀ ਹੈ
transliteration: Miti Kai Amiti Ar Sankh Kai Asankh Pouni , Laykh Kai Alaykh Nahee Taul Kai Taulaaee Hai ?
translation: As the imperishable God is beyond measurement, beyond counting, beyond perception, beyond· weighing; so is the praise of a True Guru.

gurmukhi: ਅਰਧ ੳੁਰਧ ਪਰਜੰਤ ਕੈ ਅਪਾਰ ਜੰਤ ਅਗਮ ਅਗੋਚਰ ਨ ਮੋਲ ਕੈ ਮੁਲਾੲੀ ਹੈ
transliteration: Aradh Uradh Parajant Kai Apaar Janta , Agam Agochar N Mol Kai Mulaaee Hai ?
translation: As the Almighty is limitless, inaccessible, beyond the perception of senses and evaluation, so is the praise of the True Guru.

gurmukhi: ਪਰਮਦਭੁਤ ਅਸਚਰਜ ਬਿਸਮ ਅਤਿ ਅਬਿਗਤਿ ਗਤਿ ਸਤਿਗੁਰ ਕੀ ਬਡਾੲੀ ਹੈ ॥੭੧॥
transliteration: Paramadabhout Asacharaj Bisam Ati , Abigati Gati Satigur Kee Badaaee Hai ?71?
translation: As God Almighty is absolutely marvellous, astonishing and very strange, so is the praise of True Guru. (71)
